    <h1>Drug Administration Routes</h1>

    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Route</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Oral</td>
            <td>Medication is taken by mouth, usually in the form of tablets, capsules, or liquids.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Intravenous (IV)</td>
            <td>Medication is administered directly into a vein through an intravenous line.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Intradermal (ID)</td>
            <td>Medication is injected into the dermis layer of the skin.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Subcutaneous (SubQ or SC)</td>
            <td>Medication is injected into the fatty tissue layer just below the skin.</td>
        </tr>
